theorem Topology.P3_closure_interior_of_dense_interior {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hDense : Dense (interior A)) :
    Topology.P3 (closure (interior A)) := by
  -- Unfold the definition of `P3`.
  unfold Topology.P3
  intro x hx
  -- The density of `interior A` gives `closure (interior A) = univ`.
  have h_closure_eq : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDense.closure_eq
  -- Therefore its interior is also `univ`.
  have h_int :
      interior (closure (interior A)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure_eq] using
      (interior_univ : interior (Set.univ : Set X) = Set.univ)
  -- Simplify the target set using `closure_closure` and the previous equality.
  have h_goal :
      interior (closure (closure (interior A))) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [closure_closure, h_int]
  -- Trivially, every point lies in `univ`.
  have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  -- Conclude via the established equality.
  simpa [h_goal] using this

theorem Topology.interior_closure_frontier_subset_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (frontier A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, note that every point of the frontier of `A` lies in `closure A`.
  have h_subset : frontier A ⊆ closure A := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h_closure_subset : closure (frontier A) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono h_subset
  -- Applying `interior_mono` yields the desired result.
  exact interior_mono h_closure_subset

theorem Topology.closure_interior_idempotent_iter6
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
        (closure (interior A)))))))))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  calc
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
        (closure (interior A)))))))))))) =
        closure (interior (closure (interior
          (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))))))) := by
          simpa using
            (Topology.closure_interior_idempotent
              (A :=
                closure (interior
                  (closure (interior (closure (interior
                    (closure (interior A))))))))
    _ = closure (interior A) := by
          simpa using
            (Topology.closure_interior_idempotent_iter5 (A := A))

theorem Topology.P1_closure_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) : Topology.P1 (closure (closure A)) := by
  -- First, obtain `P1` for `closure A` from the existing lemma.
  have hP1_closure : Topology.P1 (closure A) :=
    Topology.P1_closure_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
  -- Rewrite `closure (closure A)` as `closure A` and conclude.
  simpa [closure_closure] using hP1_closure
